thread.title: Fed's Williams: Sept 'very plausible' time to raise rates
thread.title_full: Fed's Williams: Sept 'very plausible' time to raise rates

author: cnbc.com
title: Fed's Williams: Sept 'very plausible' time to raise rates
text:
Getty Images John Williams The Federal Reserve could start raising rates as soon as September and lift them once more before the end of the year, a top Fed official said on Wednesday.
"September would be a very plausible time to start liftoff," San Francisco Fed President John Williams told reporters after giving a speech to the Mesa Chamber of Commerce.
Read More Fed's Yellen attacked on Capitol Hill
Inflation in his view is likely to be back up at the Fed's 2 percent target, with a 50 percent chance of being higher than that, by the end of 2016. And the U.S. economy is likely to be at full employment "well before" that.
The Fed will make decisions on rates at each of its meetings after weighing and discussing the economic data, he said.
"Right now I don't need to make that decision, we'll make that decision when we get there."
